{"title":"•Ampicilina-sulbactam(Unasyn)-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/•Ampicilina-sulbactam(Unasyn)-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"• Ampicilina-sulbactam\\N(Unasyn)","guid":"heQfs9M-UzHXujBz-pcgOQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Uso y\\NDosificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Descripción: Ampicilina-sulbactam es una aminopenicilina combinada con un inhibidor de β-lactamasa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Espectro amplio: Uso en infecciones como apendicitis, diverticulitis, peritonitis. La resistencia creciente limita su uso contra bacilos gram-negativos\\Naeróbicos. Las guías han dejado de recomendar ampicilina-sulbactam para uso empírico en infecciones intraabdominales debido a la resistencia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Dosis total diaria de sulbactam: ≤4 gm para bacilos gram-negativos aeróbicos. Sulbactam útil contra Acinetobacter baumannii en dosis más altas y como parte de terapia combinada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Dosis: Se dosifica como la suma de los componentes, e.g., 3 gm = ampicilina 2 gm + sulbactam 1 gm.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en\\NAdultos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• Dosis (infección grave, bacilos gram-negativos aeróbicos, susceptible in vitro): 3 gm (2 gm ampicilina + 1 gm sulbactam) IV durante 30 min q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• Neumonía asociada a ventilador (VAP) por Acinetobacter: 9 gm (6 gm ampicilina + 3 gm sulbactam) IV durante 4 hrs q8h\\Ncomo parte de terapia combinada (Eur J of Pharm Sci 2019;136: 104940). No usar en monoterapia por riesgo de resistencia.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en Pediatría","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Dosis (Edad >28 días): 100-300 mg/kg/día (dividido q6h)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste\\NRenal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• CrCl ≥30: 1.5-3 gm q6h","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Vida media: Amp 1. 4 hr, Sulb 1.7 hr","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"• CrCl 15-29: 1. 5-3 gm q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"11","text":"• CrCl 5-14: 1. 5-3 gm q24h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"11","text":"• HD: 1.5-3 gm q24h (una dosis en día de diálisis AD)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Vida media: Amp 7-20 hr, Sulb 10 hr","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"11","text":"• CAPD: 3 gm q24h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"11","text":"• CRRT: 1.5-3 gm q8-12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"11","text":"• SLED: 3 gm q12h (Can J Kidney Health Dis 2018;5:1)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Hepático: Sin datos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"1","text":"Efectos\\NAdversos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• Flebitis local (3%), fiebre, rash (2%), anafilaxis, neutropenia, eosinofilia (22%), trombocitopenia (raro), náuseas/vómitos,\\Ndiarrea (2%), colitis por C. difficile, ↑ LFTs (6%), ↑ BUN/Creatinina (raro), cefalea (raro), confusión (raro).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"• Rash maculopapular (no urticarial), no es verdadera alergia a penicilina, en 65-100% pacientes con\\Nmononucleosis infecciosa, 90% con leucemia linfocítica crónica, y 15-20% con terapia de alopurinol.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"1","text":"Riesgo en Embarazo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"• Categoría de riesgo FDA 1: Sin evidencia de toxicidad en humanos o animales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"• Uso durante lactancia: Concentraciones bajas en leche, no se\\Nesperan efectos adversos. Monitorear toxicidad GI en el infante.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"28","parent":"0","text":"Espectro\\NAntimicrobiano","guid":"","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"RECOMENDADO ++ (2)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• H. influenzae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• P. multocida","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"28","text":"ACTIVO + (34)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• Actinomyces sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"• Arcanobacter sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• B. burgdoferi","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"• B. fragilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"32","text":"• C. diphtheriae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"32","text":"• Capnocytophaga sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"32","text":"• Clostridium sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"32","text":"• E. coli (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"32","text":"• E. faecalis (VS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"32","text":"• Eikenella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"32","text":"• F. necrophorum","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"32","text":"• Kingella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"32","text":"• Klebsiella oxytoca (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"32","text":"• Klebsiella\\Npneumoniae (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"32","text":"• L. monocytogenes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"32","text":"• Leptospira sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"32","text":"• M. catarrhalis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"32","text":"• P. acnes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"32","text":"• P. mirabilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"32","text":"• P. vulgaris","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"32","text":"• Peptostreptococci","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"32","text":"• Prevotella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"32","text":"• S. aureus MSSA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"32","text":"• S. epidermidis (MS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"32","text":"• S. lugdunensis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"32","text":"• S. saprophyticus","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"32","text":"• Salmonella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"32","text":"• Shigella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"32","text":"• Staph coag-neg (MS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"32","text":"• Strep. agalactiae gp (B)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"32","text":"• Strep. anginosus gp","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"32","text":"• Strep. gp C, F, G","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"32","text":"• Strep. pneumoniae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"32","text":"• Strep. pyogenes gp (A)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"Farmacología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"PK/PD Índice","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• T>MIC","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Preparaciones Farmacéuticas\\NDisponibles en Chile","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"• Inyección","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"Recomendaciones de Comida\\N(Medicamentos PO)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• No aplica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"67","text":"Absorción Oral (%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"• No aplica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"67","text":"Tmax (hr)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• No aplica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"67","text":"Concentraci